    Kenneth Tangerois3 Maroc5 months ago on Google
    4/5
    The Hotel Rembrandt is good choice for a clean, quiet, well-run and reasonably-priced hotel right in the center of downtown Tangier. 
    The Hotel Rembrandt is good choice for a clean, quiet, well-run and reasonably-priced hotel right in the center of downtown Tangier.
    I stayed at the Rembrandt on my very first trip to Morocco in the early 1980s and had a room with bath and plenty of hot water and a window with panoramic view of the ocean and beach.
    The Hotel Rembrandt was the favorite hotel of a good friend, a writer and Hollywood screenplay writer who had previously lived in a villa on the mountain for 15 years. When he returned to visit Tangier, he preferred this hotel rather than El Minzah Hotel.
    Hotel Rembrandt has an air-conditioned bar and breakfast area overlooking its garden and swimming pool area, surrounded by flowers, shrubs and a few palm trees. The hotels lobby is comfortable and traditional and the staff professional, polite and efficient.
    There is a good restaurant and comfortable bar area in the back on the ground floor, with huge plate-glass windows overlooking the gardens and swimming pool, as well as the ocean and port in the distance.
    The hotel has WiFi and is heated and air-conditioned. If I were a tourist visiting Tangier, I would definitely consider staying at the Rembrandt.
    It is convenient to restaurants and shopping downtown, and within easy walking distance of the Medina and Grand Socco. But if you don't wish to walk, you can always hail a petit taxi on the Boulevard Pasteur or Avenue Mohammed V.

    About this hotel

    Less than 1 km from the beach, this relaxed hotel offering views of the Strait of Gibraltar is an 8-minute walk from the Tangier American Legation Museum and 8 km from the Grand Stade de Tanger.

    The straightforward rooms feature free Wi-Fi, TVs and sitting areas. Upgraded rooms have additional beds. Room service is available.

    There's an international restaurant with a terrace and Strait of Gibraltar views. Other amenities include an informal bar, an outdoor pool and a garden, plus a meeting room. Parking is available.
